	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-11-04T11:01:43">Sable Mining Africa Limited is a United Kingdom-based resource company. The Company is focused on the development of the Nimba Iron Ore Project in South-east Guinea. The Nimba Iron Ore Project is located in the far south-east of Guinea, in close proximity with the border of Liberia and the Ivory Coast, and approximately 800 kilometers by road to Conakry, around 80 kilometers from an existing operating railway at Tokadeh, Liberia and approximately 240 kilometers from Port Buchanan. The Company also holds a portfolio of Zimbabwean coal assets in the mid Karoo Zambezi coal basin in the Hwange mining district of north-western Zimbabwe and in the adjacent Lusulu area of the Kariba coal basin. The Company's portfolio also includes the Kpo Range concession, located in the West African Shield in Liberia; the Lubu Coal Project, which covers around 19,236 hectares, and the Lubimbi Coal Project in the Gwaai area of the Kariba Coal Basin, which covers around 16,545 hectares.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2015-12-28T04:02:50">BRIEF: For the six months ended 30 September 2015, Sable Mining Africa Ld revenues was not reported. Net loss before extraordinary items decreased 70% to $940K. Lower net loss reflects Operating Expenses decrease of 43% to $2M (expense), Other gains and losses increase from $106K (expense) to $717K (income), Impairment of other receivables decrease from $28K (expense) to $0K.</Text>
